reviews.text: O man, I am too old for this place but anyone under 25 would love this spot.  Great spot for singles to meet others.  It's like a dive bar nightclub.  Cash only thing is weird but I assume they just don't want to run 200 tabs at once since this place gets super busy.  I would recommend this spot for any younger kids.

Stopped here after being recommended this spot from a friend.  

This place was very busy, popular, and full on a Tuesday.  That was quite surprising to me.  I believe they have music every night, which is a huge plus.  I can see this spot being very ideal for a lot of folks, but for a particular demographic.

There were a few things I just couldn't get over.  The volume level of the band was absolutely ATROCIOUS.  It was SO loud, we couldn't even hear ourselves talk and we were outside, away from the speakers.  The levels were off and far too loud.  Anyone inside was clearly damaging their hearing.  This level of volume was so uncomfortable we were forced to leave and go elsewhere.    Mind you I work music festivals and large events for a living, so for the volume to be loud for me, this was quite a feat.

Also, cash only.

Place has history, great bartenders, awesome music and great beach views. Bring cash. No card. Has been iconic for over 80 years. This is a place you cant afford to miss out on when u visit laudy beach.
Good music and food, friendly environment. The staff was very professional and proficient. Live band downstairs and TVs, drinks and chill out upstairs.
A really cool dive bar across street from Ocean. Great views and good music.  Bartenders are attentive and quick to serve. A must stop when in Fort Lauderdale. Great for people watching.

Excellent experience. The ticket is $10 (cash no debit or credit card) and you get to see absolutely beautiful peices. The staff is super nice and the place is spotless (super clean show room, restrooms etc.). This is a must go!! What an outstanding display of absolutely beautiful Packard cars. There's no touching, of course, but what's nice that you can get up close to them and look inside. No velvet ropes to stand behind here. A great place to spend a couple of hours.

Excellent experience. The ticket is $10 (cash no debit or credit card) and you get to see absolutely beautiful peices. The staff is super nice and the place is spotless (super clean show room, restrooms etc.). This is a must go!!

Very interesting place. Packard vintage cars,  as well as stories and articles and memorabilia from the 1920s
 Cool place for those interested in old cars that are well preserved.

"Ask the man who owns one!" Fully elaborate collection of America's first true classic car the Packard. You won't see your modern sensor box of a car here. What you will see is American steel and basic fuel/spark engines that can still come to life with the simple twist of a crank or push-start in later models.  It's a worthwhile visit whether you're local or visiting for the day. A true motorhead's dream to see how it all started!

This is a Packard only museum. There was a very nice collection of cars and a few trucks representing all eras of Packard production. I am not a real fan of Packard, and if noted, I missed the fact that it was an exclusive exhibition. I thought I was going to a antique car museum, for that I was disappointed.

Amazing experience ! We arrived at 3:30pm on Sunday, the entrance closes at 4pm and the actual World closes at 5pm. It was perfect timing because there was almost no people and not crowded. Saw a lot of pretty butterflies and was feeding parrots.
The only thing I didn’t like is that I had to pay $4 to get into the park first and then another $32 for the entrance to the World. (There could be at least a discount or validation of park entrance)....

We've been to other like exhibits but were totally impressed with this experience. There were hundreds of butterflies surrounding you in the Paradise Adventure Aviary. If you are lucky, one will light upon your head or shoulder, but you will be checked to make sure there are no hitchhikers. You could easily spend an hour just in this one area mesmerized by all the activity surrounding you. Be careful not to step on any butterflies that have landed on the pathway. I would allot at least 3 hours to totally experience all the offerings at a leisurely pace. Do not miss the butterfly museunm and bug zoo! This is handicap accessible.

If you like being just another person in an over crowded exhibit with extortionist prices be my guest. Europe and Asia have better exhibits. 

You can breed piano keys really well but I’m starting feel like your a one trick pony in the butterfly aspect. No moths and  very few South American butterflies. In my opinion a very sterile environment.

I loved this place! Excellent learning experience with or without children. Loved seeing the butterflies roaming around in a beautiful enclosure as well as the birds they are well taken care of. Plants and the different species of flowers are unique. They also had a insect exhibit. This place is open rain or shine..

70% of this exhibit is outdoors, so be aware you will be walking!!!!

This is one of my favorite places to visit in South Florida to find a couple hours of zen. Every time I go I feel so relaxed from walking around the butterfly aviary and listening to the music while taking photos. This place is truly a must for anyone who loves butterfly's and birds. If you live in the area and think you may visit more than once, I would recommend an annual pass. Two visits pay for the pass. Weekends can get busy, especially around holidays. You also have to pay a park entrance fee on the weekends, so it does slightly increase your cost. There is also a quick service restaurant and great gift shop to spend a little extra time in.
Spacious and clean. Compatible park for toddler birthday parties.
Clean and safe
If your a street racing or model classic car buff then you will really appreciate the swap shop owner car collection. Well taken care of and cool looking.

Loved it. The things on offer were okay but u need to look to get a bargain. To the ones who own the place I'm very very grateful so see the amazing exotic cars on display. I have great respect for the cars but i did see some children touching them not knowing there worth. I hope this can be changed and i hope people can see these amazing cars on display for future generations to come. Its is a free museum but i did want to give something. I would also i has to ask about the history there should be something put up to tell about the history of the place and the cars and how they won there races too and where the came from. 
Thank you for the experience. 
Colin west

A series of high end and race cars, a number on turntables, including a Ferrari 275 GTE, "the most expensive car in the world", according to a video my son showed me.  We had lunch overlooking the cars and of course made a few purchases at the flea market
Great place to get a bargain.
Never been to a place as unique as the swap shop. You can find almost anything in this place. I will definitely come back next time I'm in Florida

Staff is awesome. Daniel was one of the best Waiter's.  Timely and informative. 
Great decor.
Management stopped by for a check on our service. Very cool.
Scallops were AMAZING!

Food was amazing,  the scallops,  the truffle fries,  the calamari.. all amazing! The prices were so reasonable especially considering how good the good was.  The service was terrific,  so many people checked on us.  Top choice of all the places I've been to here so far.

Good food, generous portions, great customer service! 

My family visited the Big City tavern because it was a short walk from a nearby Water Taxi stop. The restaurant was crowded but the service was fast and our waiter took our orders right away. They gave us a nice loaf of freshly-baked bread to nibble on while we waited. 

Our food was great and the portions were filling but the fish on my niece's sandwich was so tiny, she complained. Within minutes, the chef (or owner..) came out and apologized. He explained that sometimes the fish portions were smaller than they should be. He quickly arranged for her to have a few extra pieces of fish so she was pleased. 

Overall, our visit was nice.

This place is super cute and I love the indoor outdoor feel when you sit by the open sliders... The food for brunch is great and the unlimited mimosas are obviously a big plus... I tried coming here for lunch but couldn't find anything to eat... Very limited menu with no real vegetarian options.. Wish that wasn't the case, it's definitely my go to on that street.

Phenomenal. Got the coconut shrimp which was fantastic. I was second guessing spending $14 on it but once I was eating them it was worth every penny. Then I had the chicken sandwich with the sriracha mayo (all house made) and it was delicious. Jimmy and Daniella were so nice and the service was super fast. I'll definitely come back here next time I come through town!! Thank you!

The cheese cake factory is an old favorite of mine. My family and I would come here for special occasions when I was a child and I loved their Linda Fudge cake. They still have it!!! And it is as delicious as ever! Since I’ve grown into adulthood some 15 years later, they have switched up the menu and still have a great handle on the savory tastes they’ve always fished out. I’ll keep coming, and I’ll bring my kids here too.

The bartenders terrible attitude defined my experience. Calling the dining room manager a tool would b giving him a compliment. I could have given 5 Stars if they would have handled my complaint better. It's a great place in a great location

Big disappointment at this location.

We very much like The Cheesecake Factory , however here the food quality was terrible compared to other locations. We could not even finish our meals. 

The fries tasted like reheated, despite we sent it back and was redone. Second time the fries tasted still like a chewable gum fries. 
The portions were also seemed smaller and over spiced. 
Our main waiter was kind and helpful, however when  our food was brought out by another waiter and we asked something from him - to bring some more toasts - we never heard back.

We really looked forward this culinary experience and were really sorry for the disappointment.  We will most likely avoid the chain for a while.

Lace made our experience really enjoyable and accommodating! We were catching a flight home after our trip to the cheesecake factory and she was very helpful to make sure our service was quick and helped us keep our luggage safe. Definitely will come back when we are here again!

The food was great. Very big portions. My only complaint is that it was extremely warm inside. I'm not sure if its because the restaurant was full of people or if the AC just needed to be turned up just a little bit. But overall it was great.

This plays always has good food and the prices are fair. Two for one margaritas on Tuesday night. Live music on Saturday night. There is a bar that seats about 10 people. There is a TV. Free parking in attached lot.
Excellent service. Fast and delicious. Great place to walk to if you are going to the Parker Playhouse for a show.

The food was good. The prices are very reasonable. It was two for one Margarita night on the Tuesday we went. I would recommend Jalisco to anybody. There was a cute band playing and the overall Ambience is old fashioned Mexican restaurant.n

Authentic Mexican restaurant. Great for lunch with very affordable lunch menu. Tacos are awesome and the chicken soup with rice is a must try. Very fast for lunch and usually no wait or short wait. Ample bar seating. Portion sizes are large and food is consistent. Decent parking.

This Mexican restaurant was a jewel to find.  And the food was AMAZING.  It’s not easy to find a good restaurant like this but the food and service was perfect!!  I left very happy!  Thank you for having us Jalisco family!

I just moved to Florida a few days ago and we found this little jewel on our way to the beach. Had their brunch buffet (amazing!) it included pizza which I absolutely have to talk about. 110% authentic New York style pizza, which was to. die. for. The crust is perfectly crisp and the pizza is cooked in a brick stone oven. The staff was very attentive and seemed to anticipate my needs before I realized I needed them. We sat outside so that I could keep an eye on my new car. Afterward we decided to walk to the beach and the employees, ever so kindly kept an eye on her for us. I will absolutely be making this a regular spot for me.

This spot is AMAZING! The food is absolutely fantastic and this place inside and out just looks beautiful. I'd like whoever decorated this place to come decorate my house! Staff is very sweet and kind. Can't wait to come back!

Phenomenal food. Great atmosphere. The people were even better. I cannot think of the last time I had Chicken Parmesan and gluten free pizza this good. I highly recommend this place and will certainly be returning. The people I went with said the same things.
The location is great... The food is awesome, atmosphere is superb, inviting and comfortable, and Tommy the Gm is remarkable. Makes you feel welcome and special. I recommend everyone to try
The food is really good. Love the buffet, pasta, mussels, lasagna,fish and more. Good quality food. Customer service couldn't be better.

one of the best Spanish restaurants I've been to outside of actual Spanish countries. everything is made fresh and the plate combinations are amazing. I make sure to eat here every time I go to AC. the food is upscale in price but it's worth every penny. the view of the ocean and ambient lighting make it a great date spot too. strongly recommended

The only reason I gave this restaurant a 1 is because selecting 0 wasn't an option. My party of 6 was waiting for over an hour after being told 10-15 minutes. We watched as several parties of 5 were seated before us. After waiting for so long we were seated at two high round tables that were pushed together. The space was not adequate enough to fit our food, let alone it wasn't comfortable. As we sat down we noticed a rectangular table was being cleaned and opened. We asked our server if we could move over to the open table. Our server asked the women who are responsible for seating and they explained that the table was already taken. My party watched as the table remained empty for over 20 more minutes. As we waited we spoke to a manager regarding our issues. The manager explained that the table was reserved and there was nothing he could do for us. I would never return to a place with such poor service! I advise other people to steer clear of this Dos Caminos.

The food and service here is awesome! I am not a big fan of guacamole at ALL!! And let me tell you I would eat this guacamole all day long! Awesome food...awesome waitress and awesome staff period! Oh and the Chips was very fresh and warm when they was brought out to us!
Excellent food. Great staff. Our waitress ,Stephanie, was awesome. I highly  recommend eating here.

We came with a party of 17 and the wait staff did a nice job considering all the strong personalities that they had to deal with. The loss of star comes from the food. The food was good, but just nothing outstanding. 

My favorite item of the menu turned out to be their salsa verde that they served as an option with the chips. It was garlic forward on the pallet with a little heat in the back of the throat. It really was a great salsa. 

With that being said, it was the only memorable food item from the night.  Again, the food wasn't bad, it just wasn't anything I'd crave to come back for.

My server was sama. He was disrespectful and sarcastic as heck. Anytime I asked him a question he made me feel like I was dumb for asking such things. He is very lucky that the tip was included because I was going to give him 0. But he can have his 10.00..... change that attitude kiddo you would never make it in a NYC restaurant with that mouth of yours. But the food was amazing I enjoyed my meal and so did my family  Thanks to the chef!!!!

How do you screw up an egg? Ask them... The Omelette was basically a flat burnt yellow piece of something with raw spinach in it. I think I'll give them a one-star instead of zero because their coffee was good.

First time to Ft. Lauderdale. Walked the strip along the beach and discovered this cozy place for coffee. Excellent coffee. Decided to order a fruit smoothie to go. Was pleased they used all fruit.  Delicious!! Highly recommend!!
Fun casual fresh breakfast along the beach walk. We ate inside where it was cool. Fast friendly service. A definite step up from the hotels.
Great place right across from the beach. Food and staff was awesome I would definitely come back.

It was my first time going there and we went close to closing. The ambiance was good and the server was good and friendly.. I want to do another visit to try something else from there menu and to be earlier to see what the service will and that will tell me if i should increase or decrease there ratings.

The food was attractive and tasted good (green curry and red curry), but the service was little to be desired. Perhaps because we were there an hour before closing and they wanted to be let out early the server was cranky. The food was good, the ambiance was nice, but gosh i could have done without the rude sas
Food is great; ambiance is also nice; they were prompt with preparing meal. Staff were also very polite.

We were recommended to this restaurant, by someone who had not been there for a while.  Since that time, they must have replaced the chef.  We ordered [and paid a lot!] for a boat for three.  It included 12 limp pieces of tasteless sashimi, six pieces of sushi that included cooked shrimp and three rolls.  One was mashed salmon, another included cream cheese with the salmon and the third was unidentifiable.  Reams of shredded carrot did not satisfy our appetites.  This chef would not pass the test of a grocery store employee.

From the minute I walked in and opened my menu, my menu was filled with sauce. I proceed to order a Shrimp Green Curry. After waiting like what seemed to be forever for my food with an empty restaurant, they bring me my water in a dirty greasy glass. My food finally comes out and it was chicken green curry instead. I send it back and they never even apologized for the mix up. The food finally came, and was given no silverware. She gave us silverware and my form was crusty and gross. The food was pretty good, I ate most of it and as I got to the end there was hair in my food. Honestly, the grossest restaurant experience I had. I didn't bother to complain, because the service is awful clearly the kitchen is awful. Get it together back there. Will never return.

Nice quite place. Nice staff. Good attentive service. I had the Lunch Special Lobster Roll, but I did not like it. Other than that everything else was good. Be sure you keep an eye on your parking meter outside.

Excellent food and service. The menu has a nice variety of Japanese and Thai dishes to choose from. All of the food tastes fresh, and is presented in a lovely way. The servers are all really nice and helpful with suggestions on what to order. It's a nice little restaurant, modern, clean, and cozy. It's quickly becoming one of our favorites!
Absolutely fantastic! Excellent food. Great selection of dishes. Incredible presentation. Reasonable prices. Plentiful portioned plates. This is a must-visit restaurant.

We were looking for somewhere quick near an upcoming appointment that was not fast food. My niece and I were seated right away and ordered within three minutes. Less than ten minutes later we were enjoying delicious lunch specials. The portion size was more than fair for the great lunch price.

I met and chatted with Will, one of the chef/owners over lunch today.  Very nice, approachable dude.  The atmosphere was relaxed.  The food was beautifully presented, perfectly fresh, delicious and fairly priced.  Will be returning.

I looked them up on Google.  Close to where we were staying.  Good atmosphere, pleasant staff.  Black diamond steak was great.  Pork chop was burned on the bottom.  Every bite taste of burned meat.  Web site menu needs updating.  Steak on website says $16.  Menu at restaurant was $25.  Pork Chop is $22.  A fair price for what you get.  Party of 3 cost $85 before tip, and no bar tab.  I would go again, but was disappointed in Pork Chop and price difference from website.

A convenient location by the beach. Breakfast served untill noon, after that they switch over to their lunch menu. We had breakfast. Eggs Benedict and the Breakfast special. Prices are reasonable, food selection and quality is as expected as far as breakfasts go.  Eggs are eggs, toast is toast, the home fries were good. Service however was disappointing. At 11:55 i asked for a side of toast, only to be told that, because they started clearing everything to get ready for lunch  that request could not be met. Now if the waitress had come around at some point between the time we started eating until the time we finished,  i would've asked for my toast earlier. So here's the thing; its bread right? How much time would it take to throw 2 slices into a toaster? Needless to say my tipping generosity ended at 11:56.
Yum. Breakfast specials, great food, great prices. Very busy, get there early. Have always had good food, from burgers to apps. You won't regret it.

First time here... And as a dolphins fan it was tough.. but it was a great experience! Staff was friendly and attentive even though they were packed for the pats game. I would go again without a doubt.

Food was excellent! Service was also outstanding! The fish was cooked to perfection and so was the fillet. I also had the French onion soup, which tasted very good and even had extra baked onions on top! I highly recommend and will be back if I get the chance!
